memcapable already treats some ASCII protocol commands as more permissive
with memcached 1.6.x. Apply the same rule to the malformed delete command:
memcached 1.6.x accepts extra delete arguments and returns a normal NOT_FOUND
response instead of an error.

This keeps the stricter check for older memcached versions while allowing
the tests to pass with both the current system memcached 1.6.41 and newer
memcached 1.6.42.

Submitted to libmemcached upstream:
https://github.com/awesomized/libmemcached/pull/163

--- libmemcached-1.1.4/src/bin/memcapable.cc
+++ libmemcached-1.1.4/src/bin/memcapable.cc
@@ -1451,10 +1451,12 @@ static enum test_return test_ascii_delete_impl(
 
   execute(send_string("delete\r\n"));
   execute(receive_error_response());
-  /* BUG: the server accepts delete a b */
-  execute(send_string("delete a b c d e\r\n"));
-  execute(receive_error_response());
 
+  if (!v16x_or_greater) {
+    execute(send_string("delete a b c d e\r\n"));
+    execute(receive_error_response());
+  }
+
   char buffer[1024];
   snprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "delete %s%s\r\n", key, noreply ? " noreply" : "");
   execute(send_string(buffer));
